# HCDE 530 Project Rules

## Coding Style
- Keep code simple, readable, and beginner-friendly.
- Use clear variable and function names.
- Prefer small functions and straightforward logic.
- Add brief comments only when logic is not obvious.

## Python Conventions
- Use script-relative file paths for local data files (for example with `Path(__file__)`).
- Keep terminal output ASCII-safe for Windows compatibility.
- Use UTF-8 when reading and writing text files.
- Verify scripts run successfully after edits.

## Dashboard / HTML Conventions
- Default to standalone HTML dashboards unless a framework is requested.
- Include clear section headings and concise labels.
- Prefer lightweight, dependency-free JavaScript when possible.

## Safety
- Do not delete user files unless explicitly requested.
- Avoid destructive git commands unless explicitly requested.
